                    <h2>

                        Sepsis
                    </h2>
                    <p>
                        Sepsis is a severe infection throughout a baby's body. This is is a leading cause of death for newborns throughout the developing world.
                        Health workers need to be able to recognize this condition, provide initial treatment and refer the child to higher level care. Shot in Africa, ENGLISH, LIVE ACTION.
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="col-md-6 col-sm-12">
                <!-- Section Tittle -->
